.TH GTKCRYPTO-CLI 1 "June 2026" "GTKCrypto 3.0.0"
.SH NAME
gtkcrypto-cli \- hash, encrypt, and decrypt files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gtkcrypto-cli
.I SUBCOMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.I FILE
.SH DESCRIPTION
New encrypted files use GTC3 with AES-256-GCM and Argon2id. Existing
destinations are not replaced unless
.B --force
is supplied.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B hash
Compute one or more file hashes.
.TP
.B encrypt
Encrypt FILE to FILE.enc or the path selected with
.BR --output .
.TP
.B decrypt
Decrypt a v1, v2, or v3 GTKCrypto file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -p ", " --password-file " PATH"
Read the password from the first line of PATH.
.TP
.BR -o ", " --output " PATH"
Select the destination path.
.TP
.BR -f ", " --force
Atomically replace an existing destination after success.
.TP
.BR -d ", " --delete
For decryption, delete the encrypted source after successful publication.
.SH SECURITY
GTKCrypto does not provide secure deletion. Protect password files with
appropriate filesystem permissions.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 indicates success, 1 an operational failure, 2 invalid command-line usage,
3 failed authentication, and 4 an existing destination without
.BR --force .
